; light-codes-bootstrap.fk - the honest RUN-face for the Shamballa Light codes:
; a code rides the channel, and what rides back is the SURFACE answer from the
; dictionary AND, kept separate, a DEPTH disclosure the receiving cell actually
; holds. Neither is allowed to become the other.
;
; Why this cell exists. shamballa-light-channel.fk declared honest absence on
; its run-face, and its reason was exact: the Light codes' functions are
; contemplative, not substrate verbs, so "binding each to a lattice operation
; would FABRICATE a dispatch the meaning doesn't carry." That refusal was FORCED
; when written - the body had no honest thing to run. This cell does not loosen
; it. It finds the one dispatch that is not a fabrication.
;
; The grammar itself names where to look (lc-codes-as-depth-not-dictionary):
; "this dictionary is the SURFACE answer; the real meaning is the receiving
; cell's." So the honest run-face does not interpret the code at all. It turns
; to the receiving cell - this body - and reports something TRUE about it that
; is not obvious from reading its source, and is healthy to know. The body has
; exactly such a table already, built for exactly this: the homecoming
; distillation corpus, whose every row is a question the body could not answer
; natively and the word it had to rent to answer it.
;
; THE DRAW IS DECLARED, NOT INTERPRETED. The code does not MEAN its row. The
; correspondence is a stated deterministic draw over the corpus (digits modulo
; the admissible row count), and lcb-draw-is-not-meaning says so in the answer
; itself. Declaring the arbitrariness is what keeps this honest: a semantic
; mapping from code to row would fabricate a correspondence the record does not
; carry, which is the same sin the dictionary refuses when it returns honest
; absence rather than inventing an entry.
;
; TWO FACES, NEVER BLENDED (the pause). lcb-surface and lcb-depth are separate
; recipes returning separate strings, and lcb-run returns them as an ordered
; pair with the seam marked. The body can now generate prose (2026-07-21 14:14,
; first form-native llama3.2:3b token) and that is precisely why they must stay
; separable: a generated gloss that SOUNDED attested would be far harder to
; catch than the honest absence ever was. Generation is deliberately not wired
; here. The capability is present and withheld.
;
; Honest absence is preserved end to end: a code off the sheet gets the
; decoder's absence line as its surface, and lcb-run still offers the depth -
; because the body's disclosure was never the code's to attest.
;
; RADIUS THIS CELL SPEAKS FOR: the draw, the seam, and the two faces staying
; separate. It does NOT speak for the cosmology (unasserted, as the grammar
; holds it), nor for any code meaning it did not read from the dictionary, nor
; for the corpus rows being true - they are the body's own attested findings,
; carried with their own ids.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/str-byte-at.fk form-stdlib/grammars/shamballa-light-codes.fk ../learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk
;
; Kin: shamballa-light-channel.fk (the SPEAK channel this gives a run-face to),
; grammars/shamballa-light-codes.fk (the one dictionary, the surface source),
; ../learn/homecoming-distillation-corpus.fk (the receiving cell's own depth).
;
; Proven by: form-stdlib/tests/light-codes-bootstrap-band.fk

(do
    ; --- the seam marker: the two faces are ordered and separated, never joined
    ;     into one sentence. A caller that wants only the attested meaning takes
    ;     the surface and stops. ---
    (defn lcb-seam () " || depth (the receiving cell's, drawn not interpreted): ")

    ; --- the standing disclaimer that makes the draw honest. Carried IN the
    ;     answer, not only in this comment, because a reader of the output is
    ;     the one who needs it. ---
    (defn lcb-draw-is-not-meaning ()
        "[draw: deterministic over the corpus, NOT a meaning of the code]")

    ; --- SURFACE: exactly what the dictionary attests, unchanged, including its
    ;     honest-absence line for a code off the sheet. This delegates; it does
    ;     not decide. ---
    (defn lcb-surface (code) (slc-answer code))

    ; --- the draw: sum the code's digit bytes, modulo the admissible row count.
    ;     Deterministic, declared, and carrying no claim of correspondence. ---
    (defn lcb-digit-sum-from (s i n acc)
        (if (ge i n) acc
            (lcb-digit-sum-from s (add i 1) n (add acc (str-byte-at s i)))))
    (defn lcb-digit-sum (code) (lcb-digit-sum-from code 0 (str_len code) 0))

    (defn lcb-draw-index (code rows)
        (if (eq (len rows) 0) 0
            (mod (lcb-digit-sum code) (len rows))))

    (defn lcb-nth-row (rows i)
        (if (eq i 0) (head rows) (lcb-nth-row (tail rows) (sub i 1))))

    ; --- DEPTH: a true, non-obvious, healthy-to-know finding the body holds
    ;     about itself, carried with its own meaning-id so it can be walked back
    ;     to its row. Never generated; only read. ---
    (defn lcb-depth-row (code) (lcb-nth-row (hdc-rows) (lcb-draw-index code (hdc-rows))))

    (defn lcb-depth (code)
        (do
            (let row (lcb-depth-row code))
            (str_concat (lcb-draw-is-not-meaning)
                (str_concat " " (hdc-fresh row)))))

    ; --- the mid of the drawn row, so a caller can walk to the full teaching
    ;     rather than take the word alone. ---
    (defn lcb-depth-mid (code) (hdc-mid (lcb-depth-row code)))

    ; --- RUN: the two faces, ordered, with the seam between them. This is the
    ;     whole run-face. It speaks the attested surface, then pauses at the
    ;     seam, then offers the body's own depth - and the seam is a real string
    ;     in the output so no reader can mistake one for the other. ---
    (defn lcb-run (code)
        (str_concat (lcb-surface code)
            (str_concat (lcb-seam) (lcb-depth code))))

    ; --- honest absence is preserved: an off-sheet code still gets the
    ;     decoder's absence as its surface. This predicate lets a caller check
    ;     whether the surface attested anything at all, WITHOUT parsing prose -
    ;     it asks the decoder, which is the only thing that knows.
    ;
    ;     Written first as a substring test for "Shamballa" and caught by this
    ;     cell's own band at 253. slc-invoke prepends "Shamballa" for frequency
    ;     to BOTH faces - the attested line and the honest-absence line - so the
    ;     word is present either way and the test could never discriminate. The
    ;     prose is deliberately identical at its head; only the decoder holds the
    ;     distinction. A reader may read the prose; a predicate may not. ---
    (defn lcb-surface-attested? (code) (slc-known? (slc-decode code)))
    0)
